First of all guys I want to say a massive thank you for the years of hard work, blood sweat and tears that you guys have put in to DBZA. The quality of the writing and editing has just gotten better and better over time and we as the audience have absolutely loved every second of it.

Of course it is disappointing to find out that we won't get the Buu saga with the signature TFS comedic stamp we have grown to love. But I personally believe that you guys have had a big hand in the resurgence of Dragonball as a whole. Battle of gods, resurrection F, Dragonball super, dragonball heroes, xenoverse 1&2, FighterZ and Kakarot all came out after DBZA started becoming popular. The fact that you guys were asked to do voices in some of the games I think is a huge nod from the original creators to you guys being partly resposible for the rebirth of Dragonball.

You have been faced with a very tough decision. Whether to continue making the thing that made you popular but risk losing your income and your business, or to put more energy into your own original content and risk losing your fan base. The reality is some will go, some will stay and you will gain new fans as well, so ultimately there was only one choice to be made, and guys, you made the right one.

I can see that this decision has been hard on you but please guys don't feel bad. You have given us so much (if my theory is right, then you gave us more than you know) and a lot of people truly appreciated it. The people that like your content and your writing style will stick with you through it all. Thank you again from the bottom of my heart for DBZA, it is a true gem of the internet. And who knows, under different circumstances or if regulations change we may still see it return in the future!!

You are hilarious, and we will quote everything you say!!

snippet.textDisplay:
Am I disappointed? Sure, of course I am. How could I not be? I love DBZA. And, yeah, it’s the primary reason I keep coming back to the channel. I honestly didn’t think the Cell Saga would get an abridged ending. I figured Team Four Star was too burned out. I was pleasantly surprised when episode 60 finally arrived. And I was ecstatic when they teased season 4. Buu Saga abridged? Sweet.

So how could I not be disappointed? But I also understand. If you’re burnt out and your heart just isn’t in it anymore, the work you do will suffer. Even though you don’t want it to end, you never want something to overstay it’s welcome, no matter how much you love it.

I’ve been on the abridged bandwagon since Little Kuriboh started Yugioh Abridged. I remember Lani doing Yuyu Hakusho Abridged, Megami doing Sailor Moon Abridged, and Masako and Vegeta3968 doing Naruto Abridged. I remember when several of the abridgers got together and abridged the first two DBZ movies. And then Team Four Star was born.

It’s sad that DBZA has come to an end, but it’s not like Team Four Star is going anywhere. While I haven’t watched all the other content you’ve made (I’ve never checked out Final Fantasy Machinabridged for instance), I do look forward to seeing what comes along in TFS’s future. Personally, I’d like to see something that’s completely 100% TFS original.
